<br>
I remember when I was getting my epic, another rogue in my guild was ready as well...and we scheduled a General killing party.  Unfortunately, when she went first, some rotten luck and the aggro of a skeleton got her box eaten with no General spawn.  Needless to say she was pretty bummed (no box means redoing the rest of the epic...not impossible..but a serious downer).  So when it was my turn to pop the General, I did so and we killed him...then I let her loot him.  Some people could (and did) call me a fool for giving up my epic to her, but she had waited longer than me...and it just felt like the right thing to do.  Do I think I HAD to do that? Not at all.  Do I think that doing that makes me the best person in the world? No way.  But it felt really great... and in the end it all worked out, as she did her best to help me get caught up to that point again.  We have both had our epics for a long time now, and I know I certainly feel much better about it knowing that we helped each other rather than me just telling her &quot;bummer&quot; and watching her have to do it all over.  <br>
/shrug...  not a rule that everyone has to or does follow... but its a great feeling and I just strongly recommend it to anyone.  <br>
<br>
