<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 1) Does Verant (VI) INTEND that only SOME clerics will have their epic?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Answer: Yes, of course this is their intent. Earlier this year, their change to the RF part of the Cleric epic quest, VI has in fact greatly reduced the frequency of sprinklers entering the world. VI justified this change as &quot;reducing the bottleneck&quot; of the SolB RF camp. In reality they have created a monstrosity, which we know as &quot;the list&quot; today.<br>
<br>
<br>
Consider this; prior to the change there was no list per say. How can this be? What right does the cleric sitting in Naggy's Lair, clearing FG's every 7 hrs have to &quot;claim&quot; the RF camp?<br>
<br>
Simply put, it was understood that the cleric/guild putting the time in, keeping a force on standby to clear FG's had &quot;rights&quot; to the RF camp. They WORKED for it, they EARNED the right to &quot;camp&quot; RF!<br>
<br>
During my RF camp I had many discussions with GM's about &quot;who can claim the camp&quot; after me, &quot;I'm here now clearing FG's with my guild, I lead a Naggy raid to secure the camp, no one else is doing the work except for me and my guild etc&quot;. Their official view (as it is today) is &quot;there is NO list&quot;!  Does VI acknowledge the current RF &quot;list&quot;?. Perhaps, but they have turned a blind eye to the current dilemma.  <br>
<br>
I will guarantee you given the situation, (just as with Lodizal or any other mob) first person/guild to gain agro will win rights to the prize, regardless if poorcleric_111 was camping him for the past 5 days. Remember guys, there is really no &quot;list&quot; per say. At least not in VI's official view.<br>
<br>
VI's official take is this for RF and any other mob: &quot;First person/group/guild to have forces in place to attack the mob, and gain agro has rights to the kill&quot;<br>
<br>
My personal opinion, I do not recognize the list. It is a cop out. Why should the current RF spawn in Sky Fire be treated differently then any other mob in EQ?<br>
<br>
Lose the list, petition your GM (I have) to have VI change the cleric epic RF portion back to the old way, or something better this stupid SF spawn.<br>
<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp. GL to those on the &quot;list&quot;, you guys sure do have it easy, so quit your belly aching.<br>
<br>
