</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/usirigudernesskat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siri Gudernesskat</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowls at you rdy to attack!</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333333>(7/23/02 3:49 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thepond.com/~drummer/rgveda.jpg width=91 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DA EiE take Ragefire 19th July 2002</span><hr size=1> &quot;Does that mean you can still steamroll someone who was there before you?&quot;<br>
<br>
In a word, yes.<br>
<br>
In more words, I don't necessarily agree that that is the best way to do things.  But I NEVER expect not to be steamrolled (or whatever you want to call it) when camping a FFA mob, and nobody else should either.  If I'm camping something, and someone else decides to camp the spawn at the last minute, you had better believe I'm going to ask for help immediately, and not give him any time (or as little time as possible) to get his own group together to beat me to the kill.  But I won't be a retard and expect him to leave.<br>
<br>
Quite frankly, I never would have even considered steamrolling anyone for any FFA mob, until this crap with the RF list started.  Now I will gladly steamroll anyone on the list who thinks the list somehow entitles him to RF uncontested, IF that is the will of the Cleric I am helping at the time.  But I'm not out to get anyone;  I have better things to do than camp RF for a guild Cleric, with the hopes of steamrolling someone else.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
